Class TeamMember

  • java.lang.Object
    • TeamMember

  • public class TeamMember
extends java.lang.Object
    Class representing each member of the Team, each member is defined by their name and day of joining team. TeamMember class contains methods to return the date of joining, checking if two TeamMember are the same, and returning string representation of each member.
    Author:
    Rizwan Chowdhury

      • equals

        public boolean equals(java.lang.Object obj)
        Checks to see if two TeamMember objects represent the same person. Same person is defined by having the same name and start date. Comparison is done by checking the equality of string type name field and the. Date type date field of each TeamMember of object.
        Overrides:
        equals in class java.lang.Object
        Parameters:

        Returns:
        true if two objects are equal, false otherwise
